Protein Bars are great for meal replacement or a snack option on a busy schedule. Good source of energy with all the nutrients you need. Here are my 3 favourite bars: @biotechusa 

Zero Bar: 
Calories: 177 kcal 
Protein content: 20g 
9 different flavours 
No added sugar 
Lactose- and gluten-free 
without coating 
Rich in protein, but low in sugar 👌
_
Crush: 
Calories: 240 kcal 
Protein content: 20g 
5 different flavours
No added sugar 
Palm oil free! Yes!👌
_
Protein Bar: 
Calories: 257 kcal 
Protein content: 21 g 
8 different flavours 
No added sugar 
Gluten-free

So… I get a lot of questions about how I manage all of my businesses while producing content, travelling and attending major fitness events, giving speeches across the world and keeping up with the family. 
This video will give you an insight into how I run my day to day work with my team that are located all over the world. I explore how I use the Lark all-in-one suite @larksuite to make my business run efficiently and stay connected with my team.

To show you how amazing Lark is, I'm offering 100 supporters a chance to join me as I host a FREE Live Lark Video 📹 call on Tuesday 5th May. I’ll share my tips on fitness and running a business efficiently.
📕I'm also giving away a FREE eBook with workout and meal plans to everyone.

How to win:
1. Sign up to Lark, using the link, https://bit.ly/LarkUlisses
2. Fill in your email, then name
3. Everyone will get their free ebook through a Lark notification. The lucky 100 winners will also be sent their video link invitation through a Lark notification.
4. Join the Lark video call with me on Tuesday 5th May

Be quick as there's only 100 spots available! #ad #ulissesworld #larksuite
